<ResourcePool AllRegionsServiced="Y|N" AssociateRegionBySlot="Y|N"
    CapacityInfoAvailable="Y|N" CapacityOrganizationCode="Conditional"
    Node="Conditional" Operation="" ProvidesAllServices="Y|N" Purpose=""
    ResourcePoolDescription="" ResourcePoolId="Conditional"
    ResourcePoolKey="Conditional" ServiceSlotGroupId=""
    ServiceSupervisorId="" TransactInWorkDay="" xmlns="http://www.sterlingcommerce.com/documentation/INV/changeResourcePoolCapacity/input">
    <yfc:doc>
        <Element>
            <Description>
                <div>
				A resource pool represents a collection of resources for providing services. The resources represented by a resource pool should have common characteristics (such as regions serviced and skill sets). The capacity for providing services is maintained against a resource pool.<br>
                        <code>ResourcePoolKey</code> can be used to identify a Resource Pool.</br>
                    <Validation>
                        <Condition>
						The Resource Pool must already be present in the system. If not present:
						</Condition>
                        <Error
                            Description="Resource Pool for given criteria not found" ErrorCode="INV10014"/>
                    </Validation>
                    <Validation>
                        <Condition>
						The root node must be ResourcePool. If not:
						</Condition>
                        <Error Description="Invalid Root Node" ErrorCode="INV10003"/>
                    </Validation>
                </div>
            </Description>
        </Element>
        <Attributes>
            <Attribute Name="AssociateRegionBySlot">
                <Description>
                    <div>
					The flag indicates whether the resource pool is associated to the regions by using service slots.
					<br/>Default: <b>
                            <code>N</code>
                        </b>
                        <Validation>
                            <Condition>
                                <code>AssociateRegionBySlot</code> is set to <b>
                                    <code>Y</code>
                                </b> and <code>StartTime</code> or <code>EndTime</code> is not passed in  <code>RegionServiced</code> element.
							</Condition>
                            <Error
                                Description="Resource pool is associated to regions by slots, StartTime and EndTime must be passed in the RegionServiced element." ErrorCode="INV73_001"/>
                        </Validation>
                        <Validation>
                            <Condition>
                                <code>AssociateRegionBySlot</code> is set to <b>
                                    <code>N</code>
                                </b> and <code>StartTime</code> or <code>EndTime</code> is passed in  <code>RegionServiced</code> element.
							</Condition>
                            <Error
                                Description="Resource pool is not associated to regions by slots, StartTime and EndTime should not be passed in the RegionServiced element." ErrorCode="INV73_002"/>
                        </Validation>
                        <Validation>
                            <Condition>
                                <code>AssociateRegionBySlot</code> is set to <b>
                                    <code>Y</code>
                                </b> and all RegionServiced with the same Region are not passed as deleted when one or more are passed as to be deleted.
							</Condition>
                            <Error
                                Description="Resource pool is associated to regions by slots, all RegionServiced with the same Region must be deleted if one or more are passed as to be deleted." ErrorCode="INV73_005"/>
                        </Validation>
                        <Validation>
                            <Condition>
                                <code>AssociateRegionBySlot</code> is set to <b>
                                    <code>Y</code>
                                </b> and Priority of all RegionServiced with the same Region are not the same.
							</Condition>
                            <Error
                                Description="Resource pool is associated to regions by slots, Priority of all RegionServiced with the same Region must be the same." ErrorCode="INV73_006"/>
                        </Validation>
                    </div>
                </Description>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute Name="CapacityOrganizationCode">
                <Description>
                    <div>
					A Resource Pool is always created wihin the context of a Capacity Organization. An Organization can source services from any Resource Pools within the same Capacity Organization.
						<Validation>
                            <Condition>
							The <code>CapacityOrganizationCode</code> attribute cannot be changed. If it is changed:
							</Condition>
                            <Error
                                Description="CapacityOrganizationCode of resource pool cannot be changed" ErrorCode="INV10025"/>
                        </Validation>
                    </div>
                </Description>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute Name="Node">
                <Description>
                    <div>
					The Node that is associated with the resource pool.
						<Validation>
                            <Condition>
							The <code>Node</code> attribute cannot be changed. If it is changed:
							</Condition>
                            <Error
                                Description="Node of the resource pool cannot be changed" ErrorCode="INV10023"/>
                        </Validation>
                    </div>
                </Description>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute DataType="String" Name="Operation"/>
            <Attribute Name="ServiceSlotGroupId">
                <Description>
                    <div>
					The Id of the Service Slot.
						<Validation>
                            <Condition>
							The <code>ServiceSlotGroupId</code> must be for an existing ServiceSlotGroup of CapacityOrganization. If not:
							</Condition>
                            <Error
                                Description="ServiceSlotGroup not found" ErrorCode="INV10031"/>
                        </Validation>
                        <Validation>
                            <Condition>
							If the resource pool maintains capacity at resource level, ServiceSlots within the ServiceSlotGroup cannot be overlapped.
							</Condition>
                            <Error
                                Description="Resource pool that maintains capacity at the resource level cannot have overlapping service slots." ErrorCode="INV73_004"/>
                        </Validation>
                    </div>
                </Description>
            </Attribute>
            <Attribute DataType="Flag" Name="TransactInWorkDay">
                <Description>
                    <div>
					Applicable for resource pools with purpose <code>
                            <b>WMS-RP</b>
                        </code>. The flag indicates whether the capacities are defined and returned in terms of Work Day defined at the node or not.<br>
					Valid values: <b>
                                <code>Y</code>
                            </b> or <b>
                                <code>N</code>
                            </b>
                        </br>
					If no value is passed, the default is <b>
                            <code>N</code>
                        </b>.
					</div>
                </Description>
            </Attribute>
        </Attributes>
    </yfc:doc>
    <ResourceCalendar CalendarId="" CalendarKey="" OrganizationCode="">
        <yfc:doc>
            <Element>
                <Description>
                    <div>
					This element stores information related to a calendar. A calendar can be created for an organization or for a ship node. A calendar is created using the <code>createCalendar</code> API and managed using the  <code>changeCalendar</code> API. 
						<Validation>
                            <Condition>
							If provided, the calendar should be available and must belong to the node of resource pool or its primary enterprise. Either <code>CalendarKey</code> or {<code>OrganizationCode</code> and <code>CalendarId</code>} must be passed.
							</Condition>
                            <Error Description="Invalid Calendar" ErrorCode="INV10001"/>
                            <Error
                                Description="Node or its primary enterprise does not own the Calendar" ErrorCode="INV10032"/>
                        </Validation>
                    </div>
                </Description>
            </Element>
        </yfc:doc>
    </ResourceCalendar>
    <ProviderContactAddress AddressLine1="" AddressLine2=""
